      <scopecontent id="aspace_799c62b70a9db254a15636fae05664a5">
         <head>Scope and Contents</head>
         <p>The minimalist American composer living in Paris, Tom Johnson, talks about the composers he has known and lets us hear his favorite scores written by them. Contemporary music from a unique and personal point of listening. Broadcasts beginning on October 6, 2011, and continuing every Thursday afternoon from 3 PM to 4:30 on Resonance 104.4 FM, a London non-profit station widely heard via internet.</p>
      </scopecontent>
      <accessrestrict id="aspace_2ecf20efdfebdbbfe0ce8021cf059dc3">
         <head>Conditions Governing Access</head>
         <p>This collection is open for research.</p>
      </accessrestrict>
      <arrangement id="aspace_d581a1f1b2a2cb3632a8720418bceec2">
         <head>Arrangement</head>
         <p>Collection is arranged alphabetically by surname.</p>
      </arrangement>
      <userestrict id="aspace_30cb0d614acd96e9815191511d284a04">
         <head>Conditions Governing Use</head>
         <p>Rights and permissions for OHAM materials vary between individual interviews. Researchers wishing to publish or broadcast OHAM materials are responsible for obtaining direct authorization from copyright holders. Generally, the interviewees or their estates hold the copyright.</p>
      </userestrict>
